292
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:55,080
I was finally having fun today.

293
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,600
And you want me to work overtime?

294
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,000
Do I have no human rights?

295
00:10:58,560 --> 00:10:59,240
She...

296
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:00,800
Autopsy?

297
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:01,600
Yes.

298
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,290
She is our station's forensic doctor,

299
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:05,120
Yang Moli.

300
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,160
Hi.

301
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:08,840
Hi.

302
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,120
Qiu Ya,

303
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:13,200
are you interning at your family's newspaper?

304
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,330
I asked for it myself this time.

305
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,520
I want to write a real report independently.

306
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:19,280
So people won't say I rely on connections,

307
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:20,810
and that I don't deserve it.

308
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,120
I know of a case.

309
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:23,880
I think it suits you well.

310
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,360
You should be able to write a good story.

311
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:27,520
Really?

312
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:28,600
What case?

313
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,360
You said you found an important clue.

314
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:39,960
What is it?

315
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,680
Over by the clothes.

316
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,920
Can we talk outside?

317
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,600
No. Talk here.

318
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:48,320
The clothes are on the table over there.

319
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:48,760
Didi,

320
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,400
if you're scared,

321
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:51,960
you can wait for me outside.

322
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,400
I can review the files myself.

323
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,460
What am I afraid of?

324
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,800
As the detective in charge,

325
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,330
I must oversee the entire investigation.

326
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,960
I can't miss a single detail.

327
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:01,880
Fine.

328
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,850
Since it's your first case,

329
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,570
I'll help you get used to it.

330
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:08,240
I...

331
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,400
What about me?

332
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:10,520
I'm not involved.

333
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,920
Can I look at it outside?

334
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,440
Important evidence can't be removed.

335
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,600
You have to look at it here.

336
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,840
No way. I...

337
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:18,760
I'm starting.

338
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,220
Quiet, both of you.

339
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,880
Where was the body found?

340
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,680
The body was found on a rickshaw.

341
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,840
According to the puller, Man Dali,

342
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,700
he died suddenly during the ride.

343
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,560
The deceased is between 40 and 50 years old.

344
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,690
No external trauma to the head.

345
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:55,250
Judging from the mouth,

346
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,620
the deceased was a long-term opium user.

347
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,900
He was freshly shaved.

348
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,860
Note that down.

349
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,520
There are some bedsores on the deceased's back.

350
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,720
It must be from long-term bed rest

351
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,920
and lack of exercise.

352
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:12,880
The muscles have atrophied to some extent.

353
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,400
Forty or fifty years old.

354
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:17,840
Even someone in their sixties or seventies

355
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,570
wouldn't have such white hair.

356
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:21,290
The deceased had vitiligo.

357
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,760
Combined with long-term malnutrition

358
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,320
and endocrine metabolic disorders,

359
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,250
his hair turned completely white.

360
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:27,720
I told you so.

361
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:28,920
In this world,

362
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,720
there are absolutely no supernatural

363
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,380
white-haired blood corpses.

364
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,130
Where are the clues you mentioned?

365
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,080
What's the rush?

366
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,340
I'm about to find them.

367
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:48,760
I don't think you have any clues at all.

368
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,160
You're just making it up.

369
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:53,000
I, the Number One Little Spirit Medium of Jiqingli,

370
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,080
never tell lies.

371
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,340
Shut up, all of you.

372
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:56,490
This is work.

373
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:57,900
It's not a game.

374
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,200
What took you so long?

375
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,660
I've been dying to see you.

376
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:20,800
Stop it.

377
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:25,480
You rascal.

378
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:27,000
You're going to spill the food.

379
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,660
What good stuff did you bring?

380
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:29,220
This...

381
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,400
I'm starving after hiding here for so long.

382
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,000
Let's go.

383
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,400
No one saw you, right?

384
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,320
You were right.

385
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,320
That driver...

386
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,450
is just a greenhorn.

387
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:51,010
I scared him out of his wits.

388
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:03,680
Help!

389
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,200
Murder!

390
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:07,240
Help!

391
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,520
Just be patient and wait a couple of days.

392
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,810
Once the police close the case,

393
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:15,370
you can go back to the Zheng family.

394
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,500
Yes, ma'am.

395
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:20,650
Record this.

396
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,560
The deceased had underlying conditions.

397
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:24,800
There was little food in the stomach for a long time.

398
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:25,930
The cause of death is

399
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:28,120
poisoning from a mixture of opium and alcohol,

400
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,980
leading to respiratory failure.

401
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:31,680
Judging by the livor mortis,

402
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,800
he's been dead for over sixty hours.

403
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,380
More than two days.

404
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,760
But according to the rickshaw puller, Man Dali,

405
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:39,760
he died suddenly halfway through the trip.

406
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,020
Wang Shui and I saw the body immediately.

407
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,940
The livor mortis doesn't lie.

408
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,840
A sudden overdose of opium

409
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:48,340
is unusual for an old addict like him.

410
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:50,240
If it wasn't suicide,

411
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:51,240
then it's possible

412
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:52,720
he was forced or induced.

413
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,680
So, he definitely didn't die tonight.

414
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:02,050
And the primary crime scene

415
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:03,320
wasn't the rickshaw.
